<ol xml:id="list-abstract-vec-spaces-discovery-smul-axioms" marker="1.">
	<li xml:id="list-abstract-vec-spaces-discovery-smul-axioms-closed">
		The objects can be <em>scaled</em> by a numerical factor
		(called a <term>scalar</term><idx><h>scalar</h></idx>),
		and the resulting <q>scaled object</q> is always equal to another in the collection of objects.
	</li>
	<li xml:id="list-abstract-vec-spaces-discovery-smul-axioms-distrib1">
		Every <m>k,\uvec{v},\uvec{w}</m> satisfy <m>k(\uvec{v}+\uvec{w}) = k\uvec{v}+k\uvec{w}</m>.
	</li>
	<li xml:id="list-abstract-vec-spaces-discovery-smul-axioms-distrib2">
		Every <m>k,m,\uvec{v}</m> satisfy <m>(k+m)\uvec{v} = k\uvec{v}+m\uvec{v}</m>.
	</li>
	<li xml:id="list-abstract-vec-spaces-discovery-smul-axioms-assoc">
		Every <m>k,m,\uvec{v}</m> satisfy <m>k(m\uvec{v}) = (km)\uvec{v}</m>.
	</li>
	<li xml:id="list-abstract-vec-spaces-discovery-smul-axioms-one">
		Every <m>\uvec{v}</m> satisfies <m>1\uvec{v} = \uvec{v}</m>.
	</li>
</ol>
